Package: hls-livecam-server
Version: 2.7.6
Section: video
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ffmpeg, nginx, v4l-utils, python3, python3-psutil, python3-flask, python3-pil, wget, ca-certificates
Recommends: curl, smartmontools
Maintainer: hls-livecam-server maintainers <hls-livecam@example.org>
Description: HLS webcam streaming server with web viewer
 Streams a USB webcam via HLS using MediaMTX and ffmpeg.
 Includes an nginx-served web viewer with retro terminal UI.
 Supports Chrome, Firefox, and Safari.
 .
 On first install, run: sudo hls-livecam-setup
 To repair a broken stream: sudo hls-livecam-repair
